#)Throw
1)throw is used inside the method to explicitly throw an exception
Example
1)“If I want to manually raise an exception I use throw.
2)“I use throw when I want to manually throw an exception, like validating age or input.”
throw new IllegalArgumentException("Invalid input");





#)Throws
1)only declares the exception.
2)is used in the method signature to declare that a method might throw an exception.
Example
If my method might raise an exception but I want the caller to handle it, I use throws.”




